parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the automatic braking system can cause sudden stops, which can lead to accidents, especially if there are vehicles following closely behind. This issue can also cause a loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or slows down without warning
the warning system flashes on the dashboard
the brakes are applied without the driver's input
the vehicle may lurch or jerk forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the brake pedal can cause a loss of braking performance, which can lead to accidents or increase the stopping distance.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal depresses to the floor
the vehicle moves forward when the brake pedal is depressed
an abnormal squeaking sound emits from the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master brake cylinder can cause a loss of braking performance, which can lead to accidents or increase the stopping distance.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal depresses to the floor
the vehicle moves forward when the brake pedal is depressed
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, leading to a higher risk of rear-end collisions, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's automatic emergency braking system triggers unnecessarily
causing the brakes to engage
the "BRAKE" warning light to display on the dashboard
and a beeping warning alarm to sound. In some cases
the steering wheel may also "jiggle" to the left and right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning radio/electrical system can cause distractions while driving, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: Crackling noises in the front speakers
complete failure of sound
daily stop and start in the sound system
blank moments
and complete sound loss.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially when it occurs on a freeway or busy road.
symptoms: The vehicle dies while driving
unable to start the vehicle or put it in neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hard brake pedal and difficulty starting the vehicle can lead to accidents, especially in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the car doesn't start
requires multiple attempts to start the vehicle.
